{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Promote drug harm reduction information and services",
        "additional_details": "This petition is to promote harm reduction in the UK in the following ways: \r\n- Allow licenced premises to test drugs \r\n- Make drugs reagent kits readily available \r\n- Make pharmacies have reagents where drugs can be tested for free anonymously \r\n- Promote information on how to use drugs safely\r\n- Promote information on what to do in an emergency situation for a friend or family member\r\nThese services will cut drug deaths and save the NHS money. Statistics about deaths and usage are from drugwise.org",
        "background": "There were 3744 drug related deaths in the UK in 2016. The government currently provides no official harm reduction information or services. 35% of the UK's population have taken drugs in their lifetime. The government needs to promote harm reduction information and provide testing services.",
